  "extraHighlightWords": [
    {
      "word": "podcast",
      "pos": "n.",
      "zh": "Podcast；網路廣播節目",
      "phonetic": "",
      "level": "extra",
      "firstOccurrenceSentenceIndex": 8,
      "highlightType": "extra-high-frequency"
    }
  ],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "It was a bright, busy Monday morning, and Coco left her apartment on her bicycle ten minutes earlier than usual.",
      "zh": "那是一個晴朗又忙碌的星期一早晨，Coco 提早十分鐘騎腳踏車離開公寓。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Her aunt had already made breakfast: warm rice, a boiled egg, and a cup of milk.",
      "zh": "她的阿姨已經做好了早餐：溫熱的白飯、一顆水煮蛋，還有一杯牛奶。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Eat before you go,\" her aunt said. \"You look tired.\"",
      "zh": "阿姨說：「出門前先吃一點，你看起來很累。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco grabbed a piece of toast instead and promised she would eat the egg later.",
      "zh": "Coco 拿了一片吐司代替，答應她晚點會把蛋吃掉。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The sky was clear and blue, with a few small clouds near the mountain behind the school.",
      "zh": "天空清澈湛藍，學校後方的山附近飄著幾朵小小的雲。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She parked her bicycle by the gate and walked in, past the busy morning crowd of students.",
      "zh": "她把腳踏車停在門口，走進校園，經過一群忙碌的晨間人潮。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Every student at their school knew one strange fact: the clock above the front gate was always ten minutes slow.",
      "zh": "學校裡每個學生都知道一件怪事：大門口的鐘，永遠慢十分鐘。"
    },
    {
      "en": "It didn't matter how many times someone fixed it. By the next morning, it was slow again.",
      "zh": "不管修過多少次，隔天早上它又會變慢。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice had a new plan for their podcast. \"Let's stop asking easy questions,\" she said. \"Let's solve a real case.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 對他們的 podcast 有個新計畫：「別再問那些簡單無聊的問題了，」她說：「我們來解一個真正的案子。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco looked up from her notebook. \"The clock? Everyone already knows about the clock.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 從筆記本上抬起頭來：「那個鐘？大家早就知道那個鐘的事了。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Exactly,\" Bernice said. \"Everyone knows about it, but nobody knows why.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 說：「就是啊，大家都知道有這件事，但沒有人知道為什麼。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan agreed to let them try, but he gave them one clear rule first.",
      "zh": "潘老師同意讓他們試試看，但先給了他們一條清楚的規則。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"A good case doesn't start with a guess,\" he said. \"It starts with checking what's actually true.\"",
      "zh": "他說：「一個好的案子不是從猜測開始，而是從查證什麼是真的開始。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "So instead of asking why the clock was slow, they asked a smaller question first: how slow, exactly, and when?",
      "zh": "所以他們沒有先問「鐘為什麼慢」，而是先問一個更小的問題：到底慢多少？什麼時候開始慢的？"
    },
    {
      "en": "Every morning for a week, Coco checked the clock at exactly eight o'clock and wrote down the time it showed.",
      "zh": "接下來一整個星期，Coco 每天早上八點整都去看那個鐘，把它顯示的時間記下來。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The answer was always the same: ten minutes slow. Not nine, not eleven. Always exactly ten.",
      "zh": "答案永遠一樣：慢十分鐘，不是九分鐘，也不是十一分鐘，永遠剛好十分鐘。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"That's strange,\" Coco said. \"A broken clock is usually messy. This one is too regular.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 說：「這很奇怪，一個壞掉的鐘通常是亂的，但這個太規律了。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice's eyes lit up. \"So maybe it's not broken. Maybe someone is doing this on purpose.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 眼睛一亮：「所以搞不好它根本沒壞，是有人故意這樣做的。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "They found the school worker who repairs the clock, a quiet man named Mr. Tan.",
      "zh": "他們找到負責修鐘的學校工友，一位安靜的男士，叫做陳先生。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"I fix it every month,\" Mr. Tan said. \"Every time, it's perfect when I leave.\"",
      "zh": "陳先生說：「我每個月都會修一次，每次修完離開的時候，它都是準的。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Then how does it get slow again?\" Bernice asked.",
      "zh": "Bernice 問：「那它是怎麼又變慢的？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Tan shook his head. \"I don't know. I only know the schedule doesn't match what I see.\"",
      "zh": "陳先生搖搖頭：「我不知道，我只知道排程跟我看到的對不起來。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco wrote one line in her notebook: fixed and correct on day one, slow again by day two.",
      "zh": "Coco 在筆記本上寫下一行字：第一天修好是準的，第二天就又慢了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Someone is changing it back,\" she said quietly. \"But why would anyone want the clock to be slow?\"",
      "zh": "她小聲說：「有人把它調回去了，但為什麼會有人希望這個鐘是慢的？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice picked up her bag. \"There's one way to find out. We watch it.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 拿起書包：「只有一個辦法知道答案，我們來盯著它看。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan smiled for the first time that afternoon. \"Now that,\" he said, \"is a real question.\"",
      "zh": "潘老師那天下午第一次露出笑容：「這個，」他說：「才是一個真正的問題。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "That night, Coco added one more line under her notes: whoever is doing this is not trying to break the clock. They are protecting the ten minutes.",
      "zh": "那天晚上，Coco 在筆記下面又加了一行：不管是誰在做這件事，他要的不是弄壞鐘，而是要守住那十分鐘。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Neither of them knew yet how right that guess would turn out to be.",
      "zh": "他們兩個都還不知道，這個猜測後來會有多準。"
    }
  ],
